summary: I think is VERY UGLY the way Killing Eve shows italians. It's over the stereotype. We aren't all sicilian. In Tuscany italians...
body:
I think is VERY UGLY the way Killing Eve shows italians. It’s over the stereotype. We aren’t all sicilian. In Tuscany italians don’t speak in sicilian, pfft and… the clothes? Oh my god, we are not Godfather in ‘30s, c'mon. We wear the same things of an american, not only flower-dress and sunglasses with tradional dances

The show is in 2018, right? Well… that italian background is max '50s in “La Dolce Vita”.

Let me remind...
body:
Ok so I’m obviously behind in terms of getting on the Killing Eve bandwagon but now I am truly and firmly on it.

Let me remind you that i was a couple seasons behind on Orphan Black and I just… finished writing a dissertation chapter on Orphan Black and Ex Machina (which I actually saw in cinema with a tinder date… lolllllll) so… if this means in five years time I write a book chapter on Killing Eve I’m totally ok with that possibility.

Hannibal - one of like 2...
body:
Current favorite shows -

Adventure Time - best animated show ever made, Princess Bubblegum is amazing

Hannibal - one of like 2 pieces of visual media where the cinematography was good enough to catch my untrained amateur eye

Killing Eve - hannibal with more humor and a totally different style of execution, amazing performances from both Sandra Oh and Jodie Coleen
